Bronze Age

=Egypt: Nile river
currency
- Deben
- Kidet = 0.1 Deben
Hedjet: white crown of Upper Egypt
Deshret: red crown of Lower Egypt
Pschent: double crown: Hedjet + Deshret

#Early Dynastic Period (3150-2686 BC)
Narmer - unified Upper (22 nomes) and Lower (20 nomes) Egypt
1st dynasty (3100-2900 BC): capital Thinis
2nd dynasty (2900-2686 BC)

#Old Kingdom (2686–2181 BC): capital Memphis
Lower Egypt cities: Buto, Sais, Busiris, Bubastis, Heliopolis, Memphis
Upper Egypt cities: Heracleopolis, Thinis, Abydos, Dendera, Naqada, Thebes/Waset, Hierakonpolis, Edfu, Kom Ombo
Nome: administrative territory unit
Sarcophagus: stone coffin
3rd dynasty (2686-2613 BC)
- Djoser - step pyramid at Saqqara
4th dynasty (2613-2494 BC)
- Sneferu - red pyramid and bent pyramid at Dahshur
- Khufu/Cheops - great pyramid at Giza
- Khafre - pyramid at Giza
- Menkaure - pyramid at Giza
5th dynasty (2494-2345 BC)
6th dynasty (2345-2181 BC)

#First Intermediate Period
7th/8th dynasty (2181-2160 BC)
9th dynasty (2160-2130 BC): capital Heracleopolis
10th dynasty (2130-2040 BC)

#Middle Kingdom (2050-1650 BC): capital Thebes
Lower Egypt cities: Avaris
11th dynasty (2150-1991 BC)
12th dynasty (1991-1802 BC): built pyramids
13th dynasty (1803-1649 BC)

#Second Intermediate Period
14th dynasty (1725-1650 BC): lower Egypt, capital Avaris
15th dynasty (1650-1550 BC): lower Egypt, Hyksos kings (Levant)
16th dynasty (1649-1582 BC): upper Egypt, capital Thebes
17th dynasty (1580-1550 BC): upper Egypt, capital Thebes

#New Kingdom (1550-1050 BC)
Mummy: preserved body wrapped in linen with amulets, organs removed except heart
- Canopic Jars: urns with head-shaped lid to store organs, lungs (baboon), liver (human), stomach (jackal), intestines (falcon)
mummification: dogs, cats, ibises, falcons, crocodiles, baboons
Atef crown: Osiris cult, Hedjet with ostrich feather on both sides
Hemhem crown: triple Atef + 2 uraei + 2 ram horns + 3 sun disks
Pharaoh: divine monarch
Lower Egypt cities: Tanis
Upper Egypt cities: Amarna
18th dynasty (1550-1292 BC): capital Thebes
- Ahmose I: expulsion of Hyksos, construction projects
- Amenhotep I
- Thutmose I: conquest in Levant and Nubia, tomb in Valley of Kings
- Thutmose II
- Hatshepsut - construction projects
- Thutmose III - military campaigns
- Akhenaten / Amenhotep IV - wife Nefertiti, abandoned polytheism , new capital Amarna
- Tutankhamun - intact tomb
- Haremheb - stabilized country
19th dynasty (1292-1189 BC)
- Seti I - battles against Hittites
- Ramesses II / Ramesses the Great - battles against pirates + Hittites + Nubians, construction projects (Abu Simbel), new capital in Nile delta
20th dynasty (1189-1077 BC): capital Memphis
- Ramesses III - battles with Sea People, decline

=Kingdom of Kerma (2500-1500 BC): Nubia, absorbed into Egypt
=Land of Punt (2500-1000 BC): Eritrea/Somaliland, trade with Egypt (gold, ebony, ivory, incense)

=Mesopotamia: Tigris+Euphrates rivers
currency
- Mina = ~0.5kg
- Talent = 60 Minas
- Shekel = 1/60 Mina

#Sumer (4500-1900 BC): lower Mesopotamia
city states: Eridu, Ur, Uruk, Lagash, Larsa, Nippur, Kish, Adab, Girsu
#Elam (3200-539 BC): southwest Iran, capital Susa

#Phoenicia/Canaan (2500-539 BC): semitic, Levant
currency
- Shekel (silver)
cities: Byblos, Tyre, Sidon, Beirut
colonies: 
- Europe: Gades (Cádiz), Málaga, Malta, Caralis (Cagliari)
- Africa: Tingis (Tangier), Utica, Carthage


#Akkadian Empire (2334-2154 BC): semitic, capital Akkad
- Sargon (2334-2279): conquered Sumer
- Naram-Sin (2254-2218)
#Old Babylonian Empire (1894-1595 BC)
- Mesopotamia, capital Babylon, Akkadian language
- Hammurabi (1792-1750 BC): conquered Mesopotamia, law code
#Kassite Empire (1595-1155 BC): Babylonian

Early Assyrian period (2600-2025 BC)
Old Assyrian period (2025-1364 BC)
#Middle Assyrian Empire (1363-912 BC)
- upper Mesopotamia, capital Aššur, Akkadian language

#Mitanni (1600-1260 BC): southeast Anatolia, Hurrian language
- conquered by Hittites and Assyrians
#Hittite Empire (1650-1190 BC): Anatolia, indo-european

=Greece

#Minoan civilization (3100-1100 BC): Crete
- Knossos palace: red columns
- Labrys: double-headed axe

#Mycenaean civilization (1700-1100 BC): Peloponnese + Thessaly
palace-centered states: Mycenae, Tiryns, Pylos, Orchomenus, Thebes, Athens, Iolcus

#Anatolia
cities: Troy, Ephesus, Miletus

=India: Indus river
Indus Valley Civilisation (3300-1300 BC)
- cities: Harappa, Mohenjo-Daro

=China: Yellow river
Longshan culture
Xia dynasty (2070-1600 BC): Erlitou culture
Shang dynasty (1600-1045 BC): Erligang culture

=Late Bronze Age collapse (~12 century BC)
destroyed cities, economic decline
cultures: Mycenaean, Kassites, Hittites, Egypt
theories: Sea People invasions, Dorian migration
